be called on the Day of Resurrection as brightly radiant from the traces of ablution. Whoever among you is able to extend his radiance, let him do so.\" Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 136, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/faith-iman\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":14001,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/05\/06\/wudu-sins-erased\/","url_meta":{"origin":13998,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Wudu: Excellent ablution erases minor sins","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 6, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Uthman ibn Affan reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWhoever performs ablution in an excellent manner, his sins will depart from his body even from under his fingernails.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 245 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Muslim \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0639\u064f\u062b\u0652\u0645\u064e\u0627\u0646\u064e \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0639\u064e\u0641\u064e\u0651\u0627\u0646\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":25521,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/12\/01\/al-muwalah-fi-al-wudu-wajib\/","url_meta":{"origin":13998,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Wudu: Evidence continuity in ablution is obligatory","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"December 1, 2017","format":false,"excerpt":"Umar ibn al-Khattab reported: A man performed ablution and he left out a spot on his foot the size of a fingernail. The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cGo back and perform ablution well.\u201d The man went back and then prayed. Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 243 Grade: Sahih\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":2787,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/04\/06\/wudu-perfect-ablution\/","url_meta":{"origin":13998,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Wudu: Description of a perfect ablution","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"April 6, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Humran reported: Uthman, may Allah be pleased with him, requested a vessel of water and he poured water over his hands three times and washed them. Then, he put his right hand in the vessel and rinsed his mouth and sniffed water into his nose. Then, he washed his face\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":25581,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/12\/07\/wudu-ablution-hadath-salat\/","url_meta":{"origin":13998,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Wudu: Ablution required before prayer","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"December 7, 2017","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cPrayer is not accepted from one in a state of minor impurity until he renews ablution.\u201d A man from Hadhramaut said, \u201cAbu Huraira, what is minor impurity?\u